title: Grateful Dead Live at Rosemont Horizon on 1988-04-14
description: Jack Straw, West L.A. Fadeaway, Mama Tried-> Big River, Althea, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song, Promised Land Box Of Rain, Iko Iko, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text: Wow. This is one that has been overlooked. I'm listeing to Big River right now, and this sounds like the Grateful Dead to me.. thats for sure, jerry is yeap, Jerry. and well the rest of the guys speak for themself, i guess no one has taken time to listen to this beauty. I like it, 5 stars!
january 25 06 This could in fact be a hidden gem. The quality of the vocal sounds are really good. I mean the sound. Tight Jackstraw! May wanna take a listen to this. Jerry rips through big river.
sick. love the brent shows, this one sounds nasty so far.  jackstraw kinda rolls right into west LA and i couldn't wait any longer to write a review.  goddamn i miss these guys.

five for being there! I loved the show when I was there.  Forgot all about the fact that I was in Chicago, even.  Hell, at one point I forgot that I was even I and of course, I'm not really I and neither are you, for that matter :)

Grateful to take another listen to this one!  And a sweet Jack Straw it was!
really clear vocals are great and music sounds good too.
